{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d425a389-475b-441c-8be1-c4c3e7884002","content":"Here's the recommended setup:\n\n**1. Project file (`MyTests.csproj`)** — MSTest.Sdk gives you the simplest possible config:\n\n```xml\n<Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/3.7\">\n\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>\n  </PropertyGroup>\n\n</Project>\n```\n\nNo `<PackageReference>` needed — the SDK brings in MSTest, the runner, and code analyzers automatically.\n\n**2. Enable parallelism** — add an assembly-level attribute (e.g., in a `Usings.cs`):\n\n```csharp\n[assembly: Parallelize(Scope = ExecutionScope.ClassLevel)]\n```\n\nThis runs test **classes** in parallel (methods within a class still run sequentially). Use `ExecutionScope.MethodLevel` if you want maximum parallelism.\n\n**3. Sequential database tests** — mark those classes with `[DoNotParallelize]`:\n\n```csharp\n[TestClass]\n[DoNotParallelize]\npublic class DatabaseIntegrationTests\n{\n    [TestMethod]\n    public void Can_Insert_Record() { /* ... */ }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public void Can_Read_After_Write() { /* ... */ }\n}\n```\n\nClasses tagged `[DoNotParallelize]` run **after** all parallel classes finish, and they run one at a time.\n\n**Summary:**\n\n| Concern | Mechanism |\n|---|---|\n| Minimal project file | `MSTest.Sdk` (no explicit package refs) |\n| Parallel by default | `[assembly: Parallelize]` |\n| Sequential exceptions | `[DoNotParallelize]` on specific classes |","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"24cb427f-0c79-4eb5-8302-8a14690070d3","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The repository appears to be empty. The user is asking a general question about MSTest setup. Let me provide the recommended setup based on my knowledge of MSTest.Sdk, parallel execution, and the `[DoNotParallelize]` attribute.","outputTokens":481,"requestId":"8029:372967:17B7B62:191A64F:6A046180"},"id":"e6e1126e-8c17-440c-b2a4-ed69ed82c6b4","timestamp":"2026-05-13T11:33:37.626Z","parentId":"090594f2-